            <form>
               <orth>mearal</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Notes: “sàl is uisge ’n ceann a chéile”. Applecross: “Cho saillt ris a’ mheireal”.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_ScalpayNMacSweenslips-idp115464352">
            <form>
               <orth>stragaidh (n.)</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Notes: used of the catch of fish in a net.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_ScalpayNMacSweenslips-idp115475368">
            <form>
               <orth>sùireadh</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Notes: favourable current in towards shore, against main current. (&lt; sùgh + ruith?)</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_ScalpayNMacSweenslips-idp115479760">
            <form>
               <orth>abartach</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: duine abartach. Notes: Duine nach b’urrainn rud a chumail aige fhéin.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_ScalpayNMacSweenslips-idp115478896">
            <form>
               <orth>cuaireadh</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: Cuaireadh ort! Notes: mild malediction.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_ScalpayNMacSweenslips-idp161846912">
            <form>
               <orth>diridh-oichinn</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: Dé ’n diridh-oichinn a th’ort? Notes: used of person running about from one thing to another.</def>
         </entry>
